<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 2em;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .compression-info {
            background: #e8f5e8;
            border: 1px solid #c3e6c3;
            padding: 1em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .content-block {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            border: 1px solid #dee2e6;
            padding: 2em;
            margin: 2em 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
            word-wrap: break-word;
        }
        .stats {
            font-family: monospace;
            background: #fffbf0;
            border: 1px solid #ffeaa7;
            padding: 1em;
            margin: 1em 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1><%= title %></h1>

    <div class="compression-info">
        <h2>Compression Testing</h2>
        <p>This page contains repetitive text content designed to test compression algorithms.</p>
        <div class="stats">
            <strong>Content Stats:</strong><br>
            Original Size: <%= originalSize %> bytes<br>
            Compression Ratio: <%= compressionRatio %><br>
            Content Length: <%= content.length %> characters
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="compression-info">
        <h2>Testing Notes</h2>
        <p>Use this page to test:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>How Printeer handles large compressed content</li>
            <li>Whether compression affects PDF generation speed</li>
            <li>Memory usage with large text content</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The server should compress this content using gzip/deflate if compression is enabled.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-block">
        <h2>Large Text Content (for Compression Testing)</h2>
        <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #666;">
            <%= content %>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="compression-info">
        <h2>Compression Analysis</h2>
        <p>Check the response headers for compression information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>Content-Encoding</code> - Should show gzip, deflate, or br</li>
            <li><code>Content-Length</code> - Should be smaller than original size</li>
            <li><code>Vary: Accept-Encoding</code> - Should be present</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>